# Security & privacy

- Validate all network inputs; enforce size limits.
- No unsafe deserialization (pickle) for untrusted artifacts.
- Never log secrets, API keys, bearer tokens, full prompts, or tensors.
- Registration: do not return existing client keys without proof of possession.
- Unset `OPERATOR_API_KEY` is unsafe for production.
- Qualify privacy: data locality ≠ DP ≠ SecAgg ≠ TLS.
- Inference with `payload.inputs` leaves the node — disclose in UI/docs.
- Location: coarse + jitter only; no IPs/client ids on public APIs.
